<h3>Destroy Summoned</h3>

<p>Our final anti-summoned DD.&nbsp; It's very efficient at 1200 damage for 300
mana -- and it has a -100 resist adjustment (meaning is hard for the mob to
resist).&nbsp; If you're like me, you're wondering why this spell is called
&quot;destroy&quot; summoned when it merely scratches mobs you'll fight at this
level.</p>
<h3>Imbue Air</h3>
<p>Summons an item for tradeskills.&nbsp; Requires Air Mephit Blood to cast.&nbsp; Again, this is player-made, requiring 
air mephit blood from the Plane of Air (PoP), a raw diamond and the spell: Imbue Diamond (combine in a jeweler's kit).</p>
<h3>Girdle of MagiKot</h3>
<p>An upgrade to the belt -- this one has 500 hp!</p>
<h3>Other Upgrades</h3>
<p>A few upgrades this level are pretty important: <b>Shield of Maelin</b> --
yet another self-shield upgrade, Planar Renewal -- a 1200 point pet heal and <b>Maelstrom</b><b>
of Thunder</b> -- a 900 point rain spell (evoc-based, but checks magic).</p>
